Cache

Controller enables to store a value to a memory cache.

Gets a value stored in cache. If the key is not in cache "not found" result is returned.

Authorizations:
basicAuth
path Parameters
key
required
string

Key of entry in a cache.

Responses

https://localhost:5010/api/v1/Cache/{key}

Response samples

  • 200
  • 400
  • 401
  • 403
  • 422
  • 500
Content type
application/json
{
  • "value": "string"
}

Sets value to a memory cache with a specified key.

Authorizations:
basicAuth
query Parameters
Priority
string (CacheItemPriority)
Enum: "low" "normal" "high" "neverRemove"

The priority for keeping the cache entry in the cache during a memory pressure tokened cleanup. Specifies how items are prioritized for preservation during a memory pressure triggered cleanup. Possible values: low, normal, high, neverRemove.

SlidingExpiration
integer <int32>

Period how long (in minutes) the cache entry can be inactive (e.g. not accessed) before it will be removed. This will not extend the entry lifetime beyond the absolute expiration (if set).

AbsoluteExpirationRelativeToNow
integer <int32>

An absolute expiration time (in minutes), relative to time when a cache entry was stored.

Request Body schema: application/json
required

Key and value.

key
required
string non-empty

Key for a memory cache.

value
string or null [ 1 .. 4096 ] characters

Value to store to a cache.

Responses

https://localhost:5010/api/v1/Cache

Request samples

  • Payload
Content type
application/json
{
  • "key": "string",
  • "value": "string"
}

Response samples

  • 201
  • 400
  • 401
  • 403
  • 422
  • 500
Content type
application/json
{
  • "value": "string"
}

Connect

Controller for actions with users.

<br> Authorizes the user specified in the authenticateInfo parameter. <br> Each call to this endpoint causes a new session to be created on the application server. To authorize endpoints that require a basic authorization, you must use the returned values "UserName" as the login name and "UserId" as the password.

Sample request with a HeN account:

POST /api/connect/login HTTP/1.1
Host: localhost:53078
Content-Type: application/json
{
    "username": "username",
    "password": "password",
    "LanguageId"   : "CZ",
    "DbProfile": "test_env",
    "ServerURL" : "http://www.mydomain.cz/hen"
}

Sample request with a domain account:

POST /api/connect/login HTTP/1.1
Host: localhost:53078
Content-Type: application/json
{
    "username": "ASOL\\username",
    "password": "domain password",
    "UseWindowsAuthentication": true,
    "UseCurrentUserCredentials": false
    "LanguageId"   : "CZ",
    "DbProfile": "test_env",
    "ServerURL" : "http://www.mydomain.cz/hen"
}
Request Body schema: application/json

Info about user to authorize.

userName
string or null

Gets or sets the user name (login name or login email).
It can be unspecified when ASOL.Nephrite.WebAPI.AuthProvider.Contracts.AuthenticateRequest.UseWindowsAuthentication and ASOL.Nephrite.WebAPI.AuthProvider.Contracts.AuthenticateRequest.UseCurrentUserCredentials is true, otherwise it has to be filled.
password
string or null

Gets or sets the password.
It can be unspecified when ASOL.Nephrite.WebAPI.AuthProvider.Contracts.AuthenticateRequest.UseWindowsAuthentication and ASOL.Nephrite.WebAPI.AuthProvider.Contracts.AuthenticateRequest.UseCurrentUserCredentials is true, otherwise it has to be filled.
useWindowsAuthentication
boolean

If true, windows authentication is used to connect to HeG (System.Net.NetworkCredential are created and used to login). If ASOL.Nephrite.WebAPI.AuthProvider.Contracts.AuthenticateRequest.UseCurrentUserCredentials is true as well, ASOL.Nephrite.WebAPI.AuthProvider.Contracts.AuthenticateRequest.UserName and ASOL.Nephrite.WebAPI.AuthProvider.Contracts.AuthenticateRequest.Password are ignored. System.Net.CredentialCache.DefaultCredentials are used then.
If false, basic authentication using ASOL.Nephrite.WebAPI.AuthProvider.Contracts.AuthenticateRequest.UserName and ASOL.Nephrite.WebAPI.AuthProvider.Contracts.AuthenticateRequest.Password is used to connect to HeG.
This property must filled when default value is not specified in application settings or if a different value should be used. The application can be set such way, this property may not be set at all. Contact administrator to ensure how to authenticate if needed.
useCurrentUserCredentials
boolean

This property is taken into account when ASOL.Nephrite.WebAPI.AuthProvider.Contracts.AuthenticateRequest.UseWindowsAuthentication is true only. System.Net.CredentialCache.DefaultCredentials are used instead of ASOL.Nephrite.WebAPI.AuthProvider.Contracts.AuthenticateRequest.UserName and ASOL.Nephrite.WebAPI.AuthProvider.Contracts.AuthenticateRequest.Password then.
This property must filled when default value is not specified in application settings or if a different value should be used. The application can be set such way, this property may not be set at all. Contact administrator to ensure how to authenticate if needed.
languageId
string or null

Gets or sets the code of language (czech is CZ, slovak is SK, english is EN).
This property must filled when default language is not specified in application settings or if a different language should be used. The application can be set such way, this property may not be set at all. Contact administrator to ensure how to authenticate if needed.
dbProfile
string or null

Gets or sets the db profile where the user is to be connected to.
This property must filled when default db profile is not specified in application settings or if a different db profile should be used. The application can be set such way, this property may not be set at all. Contact administrator to ensure how to authenticate if needed.
serverURL
string or null

Gets or sets the URL of application server.
This property must filled when default server URL is not specified in application settings or if a different server be used. The application can be set such way, this property may not be set at all. Contact administrator to ensure how to authenticate if needed.

Responses

https://localhost:5010/api/Connect/LogIn

Generic functions

Generic endpoints to run functions of Helios Nephrite

Generic endpoint to call a function in Helios Nephrite by a function identifier

Body of a request can differ for every function.

Authorizations:
basicAuth
path Parameters
functionId
required
integer <int32> [ 1 .. 2147483647 ]
Example: 1

Identifier of a function

query Parameters
FolderId
integer or null <int32> [ 1 .. 2147483647 ]
Example: FolderId=123

Identifier of a folder. Folder can be considered as a context in which the function runs. This is an optional parameter for specific scenarios.

StoredParamsId
integer or null <int32> [ 1 .. 2147483647 ]
Example: StoredParamsId=456

Identifier of predefined set of parameters which are stored in dedicated entity with identifier no. 1496.

ReturnLogDetail
any (ReturnFunctionLogDetailType)
Example: ReturnLogDetail=Warning

Sets a log detail should be part of the response. Custom response can override a behavior of this parameter. Every function can have a different behavior.

Request Body schema: application/json
object or null

Responses

https://localhost:5010/api/v1/Generic/Run/{functionId}
